M|GitH|tx|mi uses GitHub to inspect existing cp for visual and structural patterns before building new ones.
M|GitH|**Us|**
M|GitH|it|Read an existing cp to understand established JSX structure before writing a similar one
M|GitH|it|Check recent commits for any ds sy changes dv made (new CSS variables, tw config updates)
M|GitH|it|Verify a cp matches what was merged — not a local-only version
M|GitH|it|Check Leo's spec issues for UI fidelity requirements before starting a cp
M|GitH|**Ke|**
M|GitH|tx|```
M|GitH|tx|get_file_contents     → read an existing cp.tsx for pattern reference
M|GitH|tx|list_commits          → check recent ds sy or globals.css changes
M|GitH|tx|get_pull_request      → rv what rj changed in a rt before building the consuming cp
M|GitH|tx|```
M|GitH|tx|---
